songs.title: What Would You Do?

description.plain: “What Would You Do?”, the early 2001 hit from New Jersey-based trio City High, is told from the perspective of a man who encounters a stripper at a party who he had known in junior high, and discovers that said stripper’s occupation hides a much more tragic life than the man’s outside impressions initially gave.

songs.full_title: 15 Will Get You 20 by City High
songs.title: 15 Will Get You 20

description.plain:
This song is discussing the punishments for having a relationship with an underage person. The protagonist doesn’t bother to ask and assumes an age of at least 18. City High warns against this.

Interestingly enough, band members Robbie Pardlo and Claudette Ortiz started dating when they were 18 and 16, respectively.

description.plain: “City High Anthem” is a song recorded by American hip trio City High from their self-titled debut studio album City High. It was released on February 25, 2002 as the third and final single from the album through Interscope Records. The song did not chart as well in 2002.

songs.full_title: Cats And Dogs by City High
songs.title: Cats And Dogs

description.plain: Though it isn’t certain this song intentionally mirrors real life, Claudette Ortiz has revealed that she and Robby Pardlo were an item, but the relationship was an abusive one, both physically and emotionally. The band’s management asked Ortiz not to break up with Pardlo, but they were finished before the album was. Ortiz told her side of the story in 2010 after Pardlo blamed his substance abuse problem on her and other band member Ryan Toby on an episode of A&E’s Intervention.
